% ============================================================
% references.bib
% Provenance and research sources for the VVUQ-05 full-bill (LaTeX),
% H. R. 9510 Bill v3.0, the finished visual amendment.
%
% This file carries the full operative-authority and research-influence set from
% Bill v2.0 (the VVUQ-04 final-bill) unchanged, so every key the bill body cites
% still resolves, and it ADDS the v3.0 layer: the VVUQ-01 through VVUQ-04 record
% and the VVUQ-05 update-bill inputs that this visual draft synthesizes, the U.S.
% House process and Congressional Research Service sources that ground the
% submission-deliverables appendix (Appendix B), and the explainability sources
% behind the new-standard appendix (Appendix C).
%
% A finished congressional amendment carries no bibliography; its operative text
% cites authority inline by United States Code, Code of Federal Regulations, and
% Public Law numbers. This file backs only the research-aid matter: the SEC. 2
% findings, the appendices (the visual evidence, the deliverables, the
% explainability standard, and the research-influence matrix), the development
% transparency statement, and the Provenance and Research Sources appendix, so
% the operative sections stay clean while every source remains auditable.
%
% House conventions (carried from the instruct-bill .bib files): a bare doi
% field where a DOI exists; a single resolver or canonical url; a note that
% opens with "DOI: <doi>." when a DOI exists and ends with the clickable link in
% \url{...}; no howpublished field; no duplicate link across the set. Rendered
% with ieeetr, which prints the note. Operative-authority keys mirror the keys
% used in papers/VVUQ-04/instruct-bill so the resolution is stable. Research
% influences (executive actions and 119th Congress bills) appear only in the
% findings narrative and Appendix A, never in operative bill text.
% ============================================================

